'''-{zh-cn:蒂莫西;zh-tw:提摩西;zh-hk:添莫菲;}-·尤金·「蒂姆」·斯科特'''（{{lang-en|'''Timothy Eugene "Tim" Scott'''}}；{{bd|1965年|9月19日}}），是一位美國[[共和黨_(美國)|共和黨]][[政治人物|政治人物]]，现任[[美國參議院|美國參議員]]。

== 经历 ==
2010年，斯科特當選[[美國眾議院|美國眾議院]][[南卡羅萊納州第一國會選區|南卡羅萊納州第一國會選區]]代表議員，任期由2011年到2013年，是自1897年以來第一位來自南卡羅萊納州的共和黨[[非裔美国人|非洲裔]]議員<ref name="daily caller">{{cite news|url=https://dailycaller.com/2010/11/02/tim-scott-first-black-republican-elected-to-congress-from-the-south-since-reconstruction/|title=Tim Scott: first black Republican elected to Congress from the South since Reconstruction|author=Caroline May|date=November 2, 2010|work=The Daily Caller|accessdate=July 29, 2011}}</ref>。

2013年，斯科特由{{le|南卡羅萊納州州長|Governor of South Carolina|州長}}[[妮琪·海利|妮琪·海利]]指定填補[[吉姆·德敏特|吉姆·德敏特]]的空缺而成為代表[[南卡羅萊納州|南卡羅萊納州]]的[[美國參議院|聯邦參議員]]<ref name="NYTimesZeleny12172012">{{cite news|authorlink=Jennifer Steinhauer|first=Jennifer |last=Steinhauer|author2=Zeleny, Jeff | url=http://thecaucus.blogs.nytimes.com/2012/12/17/tim-scott-to-be-named-for-empty-south-carolina-senate-seat-republicans-say/|title= Tim Scott to Be Named for Empty South Carolina Senate Seat, Republicans Say|newspaper=[[New_York_Times|New York Times]]|date=December 17, 2012}}</ref>，2014年赢得补选，2016年当选连任。他是一名財政和文化保守派人物，也贊同[[茶党运动|茶黨]]團體<ref name=CQRollGuide>{{cite news | title = Guide to the New Congress | date = November 4, 2010 | url = http://innovation.cq.com/newmember/2010elexnguide.pdf | work = [[Roll_Call|CQ Roll Call]] | page = 59 | accessdate = July 31, 2011 | deadurl = yes | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20110708200600/http://innovation.cq.com/newmember/2010elexnguide.pdf | archivedate =2011-07-08}}</ref><ref name="SC elects">{{cite news|url=http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2010/11/02/AR2010110207838.html|title=SC elects black GOP congressman; 1st since 2003|work=The Washington Post|date=November 2, 2010|agency=The Associated Press|accessdate=July 29, 2011}}</ref>。他是第一位来自南卡罗莱纳州的非洲裔参议员、1881年以来第一位在[[美國南部|美國南部]]当选的非洲裔参议员。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Political firsts: How history was made this midterm election|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/nation-now/2014/11/05/historical-firsts-from-the-election/18523511/|accessdate=2019-10-18|date=2014-11-05|last=Deutsch|first=Lindsay|work=USA TODAY|language=en|archive-date=2015-04-24|archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6Y2JALz7d?url=http://www.usatoday.com/story/news/nation-now/2014/11/05/historical-firsts-from-the-election/18523511/|dead-url=no}}</ref>


